  "time_ut": 1661061828,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0daf\u0dd6\u0dc2\u0dab\u0dba\u0da7 \u0d91\u0dbb\u0dd9\u0dc4\u0dd2\u0dc0 \u0db4\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0da7 \u0db6\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3 \u0db8\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0daf\u0dac\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db8\u0dca \u0daf\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1 \u0d91\u0db4\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Do not punish the people who took to the streets against corruption",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Parliamentarian Patali Champika Ranawaka said in Kandy that it is not acceptable to punish the people who took to the streets to protest against the destruction of their lives due to the bankruptcy of the government officials and politicians who bankrupted the country while they were at large.",
        "He emphasized that while speaking to the media after a party meeting held at the Devon Hotel in Kandy where he further said:",
        "The current government's challenge is to win the trust of the people. For that, the repression should be stopped. There is no objection to preventing someone from breaking the law. The law should apply equally and justly to all.",
        "The Rajapaksas, who started to lead this country to the abyss, have once again come to the political arena and get to know how they are doing. They are trying to continue their corrupt practices again.",
        "The responsibility of building the future multi-party or all-party government without the corrupt and the Rajapaksas is assigned to the President. If not, the basic trust may be broken.",
        "The people of the country hope for a country freed from the politicians who were accused of corruption and who intervened to bankrupt the country. Otherwise, no matter what kind of repression the government carries out, the people will turn to struggle."
      ],
